 in 1180, and in <i>-ynghame</i>, first recorded in 1227, represent a gradual assimilation to the English placename element <i>-ingham</i>.","Irish: surname adopted from Gaelic <b>Ó Cuinneagáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cuinneagán</i>’, a personal name from a double diminutive of the Old Irish personal name <i>Conn</i> meaning ‘leader, chief’. This name is also adopted for <b>Ó Connacháin</b>, a variant of <b>Ó Connagáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Connagán</i>’, from a diminutive of the personal name <i>Conn</i>.","History: A family of this name (see 1 above) can be traced back to Wernebald de Cunynghame, who was granted the manor of Cunningham by Hugh de Morville in the early 12th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Cunigan","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish or Irish   Cunningham  ."]},{"name":"Conahan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Cormac.","Scottish (Lanarkshire) and Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Connachaín</b> (see   Cunningham  )."]},{"name":"Conaghan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Cormac, Fergal.","Scottish (Lanarkshire and Renfrewshire) Irish (Donegal): from <b>Ó Connacháin</b>, a variant of <b>Ó Connagáin</b>, see   Cunningham  ."]},{"name":"Cuningham","meanings":["Scottish and Irish: variant of   Cunningham  ."]},{"name":"Cummingham","meanings":["(1997: 117;2007: 199; 2010: NA)","Scottish and Irish: variant of   Cunningham  ."]},{"name":"Cunnigham","meanings":["(2007: 429; 2010: NA)","Scottish and Irish (Donegal): variant of   Cunningham  ."]}]},{"name":"Marion","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Marion Cunningham was born in 1506, in Glencairn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland. She had at least 1 daughter with Thomas McGowan. She died on 7 November 1534, in Renfrewshire, Scotland, at the age of 28."},"et":{"1506–7 November 1534":"1506–7. november 1534","1508–1563":"1508–1563","1533–1585":"1533–1585","1506–1534":"1506–1534","1534":"1534","1533":"1533","1585":"1585","1563":"1563","7 November 1534":"7. november 1534","1508":"1508","1506":"1506","Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland","Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrewshire, Scotland","Glencairn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Glencairn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1506–7 November 1534":"1506–7. marraskuuta 1534","1508–1563":"1508–1563","1533–1585":"1533–1585","1506–1534":"1506–1534","1534":"1534","1533":"1533","1585":"1585","1563":"1563","7 November 1534":"7. marraskuuta 1534","1508":"1508","1506":"1506","Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland","Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrewshire, Scotland","Glencairn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Glencairn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1506–7 November 1534":"1506–7 novembre 1534","1508–1563":"1508–1563","1533–1585":"1533–1585","1506–1534":"1506–1534","1534":"1534","1533":"1533","1585":"1585","1563":"1563","7 November 1534":"7 novembre 1534","1508":"1508","1506":"1506","Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Écosse","Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrewshire, Écosse","Glencairn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Glencairn, Dumfriesshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Marion Cunningham est née en 1506, à Glencairn, Dumfriesshire, Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Thomas McGowan. Elle est décédée le 7 novembre 1534, à Renfrewshire, Écosse, à l’âge de 28 ans."},"de":{"1506–7 November 1534":"1506–7. November 1534","1508–1563":"1508–1563","1533–1585":"1533–15